Detailed Description

Object with identifier

The Object class defines object that needs to have and identifier, reference counter.

bool Util::ObjectId::release (  )  [inline]

Release a reference to the object. The method is a support to implement reference counting on object. It is to the responsability of the caller to destroy non usefull object. An invocation of this method is atomic with respect to other invocations of release or acquire.

Return values:
true iff no more reference exist on the object (it could be deleted)
false iff it exists at least one reference on the object
